1
00:00:01,451 --> 00:00:06,451
CHAIN-OF-COMMAND. Authorization is a graph walk over the actual Marine ORBAT.

2
00:00:06,452 --> 00:00:16,452
AGORA does role and attribute. This does relationship. Marines actually work via OPCON, TACON, attached, detached.

3
00:00:16,455 --> 00:00:26,455
Twenty-eight ORBAT nodes, 140 relationship edges. Hero query: LCpl Smith, a rifleman in 3rd Squad, asks for the INDOPACOM Posture Brief.

4
00:00:26,038 --> 00:00:46,038
RBAC denies — role not on the staff list. ABAC denies — unit attribute not a need-to-know unit. ReBAC walks the graph: ATTACHED to 2/2, DETACHED to 24th MEU, OPCON to USINDOPACOM. ALLOW.

5
00:00:46,079 --> 00:01:06,079
Operator changes the 24th MEU OPCON from USINDOPACOM to USCENTCOM. Same query. Smith's verdict flips to DENY. RBAC and ABAC do not notice — they never looked at OPCON.

6
00:01:05,769 --> 00:01:20,769
Same code path. Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL and the engine runs inside the SCIF. The ReBAC compute is local Python — no data ever leaves the boundary.

7
00:01:20,777 --> 00:01:30,777
CHAIN-OF-COMMAND. Built on the Kamiwaza Stack. Deploy in hours, not months.
